msgid ""
"Persist Klein for Ray checkpoints to local filesystems, S3-compatible "
"storage, or Google Cloud Storage."
msgstr "将 Klein for Ray 检查点持久化到本地文件系统、兼容 S3 的存储或 Google Cloud Storage。"

msgid "Durable checkpoint storage"
msgstr "持久检查点存储"

msgid ""
"Klein keeps mutation-heavy keyed state in task-local RocksDB, optionally "
"caches large immutable barrier snapshots in Ray's Object Store, and persists "
"completed checkpoints to a durable filesystem or object store. Ray object "
"spilling is a capacity mechanism; it is not a replacement for checkpoints."
msgstr "Klein 将频繁变更的键控状态保存在任务本地 RocksDB 中，可选择在 Ray Object Store 中缓存大型不可变屏障快照，并将完成的检查点持久化到持久文件系统或对象存储。Ray 对象溢写是一种容量机制，不能替代检查点。"

msgid "Configure checkpoint storage"
msgstr "配置检查点存储"

msgid ""
"`execution.checkpointing.dir` accepts a local path, `file://` URI, or any "
"checkpoint filesystem supported by PyArrow. Klein explicitly supports S3 and "
"Google Cloud Storage, including S3-compatible stores through `execution."
"checkpointing.storage-options`."
msgstr "`execution.checkpointing.dir` 接受本地路径、`file://` URI 或 PyArrow 支持的任何检查点文件系统。Klein 明确支持 S3 和 Google Cloud Storage，也可通过 `execution.checkpointing.storage-options` 支持兼容 S3 的存储。"

msgid ""
"PyArrow's normal credential chain is used when explicit storage options are "
"absent. Prefer workload identity, instance roles, or environment-managed "
"credentials instead of embedding secrets in application configuration."
msgstr "未显式提供存储选项时，将使用 PyArrow 的常规凭据链。请优先使用工作负载身份、实例角色或环境管理的凭据，不要把密钥嵌入应用配置。"

msgid "How are checkpoints organized?"
msgstr "检查点如何组织？"

msgid "Every job has an isolated directory below the configured root:"
msgstr "每个作业在配置的根目录下都有独立目录："

msgid ""
"`chk-N/` is durable metadata revision `N`. A revision contains the latest "
"completed state known when it was published; source barrier IDs remain part "
"of that metadata and are not reused as directory identifiers."
msgstr "`chk-N/` 是持久元数据修订版 `N`。一个修订版包含发布时已知的最新完成状态；数据源屏障 ID 仍是该元数据的一部分，不会复用为目录标识符。"

msgid ""
"`shared/` contains content-addressed state reusable by multiple checkpoints."
msgstr "`shared/` 包含可由多个检查点复用的内容寻址状态。"

msgid ""
"`taskowned/` contains state whose lifecycle is owned by a task rather than "
"ordinary checkpoint retention."
msgstr "`taskowned/` 包含生命周期由任务所有，而不是由常规检查点保留策略管理的状态。"

msgid "`chk-N/_metadata` is the only checkpoint completion marker."
msgstr "`chk-N/_metadata` 是唯一的检查点完成标记。"

msgid ""
"`_latest` accelerates lookup but is not authoritative. Recovery falls back "
"to scanning readable `chk-N/_metadata` objects when the pointer is stale, "
"missing, or corrupt."
msgstr "`_latest` 可加速查找，但不是权威信息。若该指针已过期、缺失或损坏，恢复会回退为扫描可读的 `chk-N/_metadata` 对象。"

msgid ""
"Job and operator identifiers are percent-encoded as individual path "
"components so user-provided names cannot escape the checkpoint root."
msgstr "作业和算子标识符会分别作为路径组件进行百分号编码，因此用户提供的名称无法逃逸检查点根目录。"

msgid "How does Klein publish and recover a checkpoint?"
msgstr "Klein 如何发布和恢复检查点？"

msgid ""
"Klein writes immutable state objects first and publishes `_metadata` last. A "
"failure before that final write leaves an incomplete directory that recovery "
"ignores. On local filesystems metadata publication uses a temporary file and "
"an atomic rename. On S3/GCS it uses one final object PUT; Klein does not "
"emulate a rename because object-store rename is a copy-and-delete operation."
msgstr "Klein 先写入不可变状态对象，最后发布 `_metadata`。最终写入前发生故障会留下不完整目录，恢复时会忽略它。在本地文件系统上，元数据发布使用临时文件和原子重命名；在 S3/GCS 上则使用一次最终对象 PUT。Klein 不模拟重命名，因为对象存储的重命名实际是复制后删除。"

msgid ""
"Checkpoint metadata also carries prepared two-phase sink committables. The "
"coordinator publishes those transactions only after `_metadata` is durable "
"and replays an idempotent commit after recovery when publication was "
"interrupted. Checkpoint-aware source offsets are notified after sink "
"publication, preserving the end-to-end ordering between input progress and "
"output visibility."
msgstr "检查点元数据还携带已准备的两阶段 Sink 可提交项。协调器仅在 `_metadata` 持久化后发布这些事务；若发布被中断，恢复后会重放幂等提交。具备检查点感知能力的数据源偏移量在 Sink 发布后才会收到通知，从而维持输入进度与输出可见性之间的端到端顺序。"

msgid ""
"State entries carry their serialized size and SHA-256 checksum. Recovery "
"checks both before deserializing a value. Retention deletes only old `chk-N/"
"` directories and leaves `shared/` and `taskowned/` intact for their "
"separate lifecycles. Checkpoint metadata has one current schema version; "
"incompatible pre-revision metadata is rejected explicitly instead of being "
"guessed or silently upgraded during recovery."
msgstr "状态条目包含序列化大小和 SHA-256 校验和，恢复会在反序列化值之前校验两者。保留策略只删除旧的 `chk-N/` 目录，`shared/` 和 `taskowned/` 按各自生命周期保留。检查点元数据只有一个当前模式版本；不兼容的旧修订元数据会被明确拒绝，不会在恢复时猜测或静默升级。"

msgid ""
"The layout follows Flink's filesystem checkpoint storage conventions: "
"[checkpoint storage](https://nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-stable/"
"docs/ops/state/checkpoints/) and [`_metadata` completion marker](https://"
"nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-stable/api/java/org/apache/flink/"
"runtime/state/filesystem/AbstractFsCheckpointStorageAccess.html)."
msgstr "此布局遵循 Flink 的文件系统检查点存储约定：[检查点存储](https://nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-stable/docs/ops/state/checkpoints/)和 [`_metadata` 完成标记](https://nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-stable/api/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/state/filesystem/AbstractFsCheckpointStorageAccess.html)。"

msgid ""
"See [Restore and rescale a job](checkpoint-recovery.md) for checkpoint "
"selection, `execution.savepoint.path`, compatibility checks, resubmission, "
"and post-restore validation."
msgstr "有关检查点选择、`execution.savepoint.path`、兼容性检查、重新提交和恢复后验证，请参阅[恢复作业并调整并行度](checkpoint-recovery.md)。"
